Popular Social Critic and Political Commentator, Farooq Kperogi has stated that the political base of APC national leader and Former Governor of Lagos state, Bola Ahmed Tinubu has ‘completely collapsed’. Kperogi, who is known for his political write-ups and opinion, made the statement on Twitter while reacting to recent bitter feud between Tinubu and the current minister of interior and Ex-osun governor, Rauf Aregebesola. Kperogi wrote; “It appears like Tinubu’s previously impregnable political base has now totally collapsed. He has lost his mystique & is now openly challenged and even mocked by previous loyalists such as Rauf Aregbesola.” “His inner circle is peopled by “traitors” who habitually leak unflattering info to the public about his health struggles. And his PR team is a crying disaster of ineptitude.” “Well, every beginning has an end. I think this is the end for Tinubu, but it’s an embarrassing end.” •President Muhammadu Buhari and Bola Ahmed Tinubu The political coalition between Muhammadu Buhari’s CPC and Bola Tinubu’s ACN has all but collapsed. There was nothing even remotely surprising about it. In previous columns, media interviews, and social media updates, I predicted that this would happen. For example, in my June… In "Opinion" •Asiwaju Bola Tinubu Everything about Tinubu — from his very name to his claims of being from Lagos State, from his source of income to his parentage — is an elaborately fraudulent scheme. Pastor Tunde Bakare’s trending video on Bola Ahmed Tinubu, for which he is receiving caustic flak from… In "Opinion" There is probably no “indigenous” Lagos family that is more famous than the Tinubu family. But, although the family is now clearly culturally Yoruba, its ethnic provenance is traceable to what is now Borno State, according to Lagos historians, underscoring the historical and sociological inaccuracy of notions of ethnic purism… In "Opinion"